b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48417.htm)  [Next](sbe48419.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n34\\. So much; on account of reflection.\n\nOnly so much, i.e. only those qualities which have to be included in all\nmeditations on Brahman, without which the essential special nature of Brahman\ncannot be conceived, i.e. bliss, knowledge, and so on, characterised by\nabsence of grossness and the like. Other qualities, such as doing all works\nand the like, although indeed following their substrate, are explicitly to be\nmeditated on in special meditations only.--Here terminates the adhikara _n_ a\nof 'the idea of the Imperishable.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 35. Should it be said that the former reply refers to that Self to\nwhich the aggregate of material things belongs...](sbe48419.htm)\n\n"